>Peldor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Thane</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#330000>(6/21/01 11:57:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Yes, Talanos is the one to ask. He makes all me bows. I'm not so sure what rogues use to pull, I think some use throwing weapons, but again, I'm not sure. I have fletching up to 103 now, but don't know the first thing about making bows, just arrows.  <p>Haladek Durgalann<br>Dwarven Paladin of MacLear<br><img src="http://www.clanmaclear.com/images/Haladeksig3.gif" border="0"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uyshtar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yshtar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(6/21/01 3:59:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Yshtar is also progressing very well in fletching...  Master at 104 now...  Need cash  to get better..  anyway, I hope to start makin bows around 150 or so...  can make some pretty good arrows now, so if ya need 'em gimmie a holler in game. I'll be in as Rashaelle most likely (she's makin better money that Ysh) and I'll see what I can piece together fer ya. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uambrodelsilvanos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ambrodel Silvanos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(6/21/01 5:05:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Talanos is around 146-148 skill in Fletching. <br>Most Rogues I've seen use throwing items to pull, but not sure what. My Rogue, Dalthon, use Shirukens (sp?) but the Range is god-aweful. You partically have to be standing on them to hit them. <br>Tal can make you a Bow and a bag full of arrows. My suggestion would be to go with Range over Damage. Tal has a Bow with 150 Range and uses Arrows with, I believe, 100 Range. Add those together and you can pull a MoB from quite far away.<br>As a matter of fact, I think he has a RoughElm Recurve in bank. It has a fast delay and decent Range. I'll work on the arrows and hopefully have them ready by this weekend.<br>If you need references on Tal's work, ask Joeker. Tal made him bags of arrows from about a year  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   btw, if anyone needs some just let Ambro know and Tal will get to work on them.<br>Tyrislor was asking the other night about Imbued Northman Earrings (I think that's what they're called). Does Kahlan know anything about those?<br><br><br>Ambrodel Silvanos<br>Noble Enchanter of Clan MacLear<br>Member of Chief's Council<br><br>aka Talanos MacLear <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ujaliawolfsdottir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jalia Wolfsdottir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Administratrix</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#330000>(6/21/01 5:16:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Yes, I made a pair of those earrings for Bruin not too long ago. Tryis, if you can get the ivorys I'd be happy to make you a pair...<br><br>And thanks Tal, that would be cool. I've read that it's best to keep both throwing and archery up, so I figured I'd better start practicing... <p><IMG SRC="http://www.bdffl.com/duffl/amy/kahlan_black.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utyris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyris</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#330000>(6/21/01 6:38:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> ok sis just tell me when i got some in bank i can imbue <p><img src="http://members.home.net/geist22/sigs/tyrislor.gif" border"1"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gwenllianmacrhuad>Gwenllian MacRhuad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#330000>(6/21/01 10:37:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Bah! Bows and arrows are for sissy girls!<br><br>*Whispers to Ambro* When ya' got some time, can I get some good range arrows?<br><br>Gwen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=scathach>Scathach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#330000>(6/22/01 3:43:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> The best fletching guide i ever found is Aoenla´s Fletching Guide:<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~ewj/fletchguide/">members.bellatlantic.net/...etchguide/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>I started fletching with Anfortas late in his life, nevertheless fletching went up quite fast and I really like it in the meantime. Brought him to some 120 skill but I will stop there now since it will be too expensive from now on and doesn´t make sense for a warrior. For warriors and rogues it is not necessary to have a better skill since what you need is a bow with a good range and good arrows with a high range, don´t bother with the delay, that´s only important for rangers. <br>I am now using a Rough Ashwood Bow (trivial at 129, range 100, damage 16, cost about 20 pp per try) and a sort of Class II arrows (trivial at 68, Range 150, Damage 2, Field Point, Bone Shaft, Parabolic Fletch, Small Nocks, cost about 6gp per 5 arrows). That´s quite good for a warrior and also for rogues.<br>When training always remember that you raise your skill with arrows, bows are too expensive for that. And if you make some arrows with a small range like 25 to 100 for skill raise: sell them to the merchant, don´t use them. Only use the arrows with the larger range.<br>Ah, and don´t forget the side effect since some patches ago: if you are using a trade skill your groupmembers will get a success or failure message. So if you don´t like your groupmembers, start fletching in the downtime. You will soon get standing ovations.<br> <p><TABLE><TR><TD>Anfortas Arondight<br> <i>31st Warrior</i><br>Clan MacLear</TD><TD>     </TD><TD>Scathach MacLear<br> <i>52nd Druidess</i><br>Crusaders of the High Plains<br>Warden of Tunare</TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gaheris>Gaheris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#330000>(6/22/01 3:54:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Kahlan,<br><br>just start fletching with your little rogue right away, every self made arrow is much better as those from the merchants, and have Zoul or Tal make her a decent bow, with a range of 100+. Thats what Stine used til she was 45, then i bought her a mrylokar bracer (summons throwing daggers), and began throwing, the skillraises very quick if you just stand in DL at the Northwall and throw several hundred daggers into the mobs fought there. Sure a bow would still be way better, in range and damage, but well, now she doesnt have to carry arrows and stuff for fletching new ones with her. Also, rogues are meant to use throwing weps, cause they get nice deadly strikes and crits with them, and, umm, at 60 the assassinate discipline works with throwing weps too =P.<br><br>Just my thoughts on this, have fun with your little rogue, <br><br>Gaheris MacLear aka Papa Bear (YESSSSSS finaly have that spell =) )<br>55th Luminary and<br>Crusader of the High Planes <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=timo>Timo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#330000>(6/22/01 8:53:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Greetings and what not ...<br><br>To settle your questions on why rogues use throwing weapons rather than bows ... although personally I use a bow ...<br><br>At mid -lvls , rogues gain the abilty to &quot;crit &quot; with certain thrown weapons ... now this &quot;crit&quot; is about the same damage a good bow and arrow does, but has a penalty of having to come from behind a mob.  Plus, you can throw when closer to a mob ... no such luck with a bow<br><br>That is why most rogues keep their throwing ability up.<br><br>Now that is all the rogue-like information I will divulge today.<br><br>Timo Nas<br>Devilish rogue of Clan MacLear   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dawnia>Dawnia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#330000>(6/27/01 11:19:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> I thought rogues were the best at throwing of all the classes. My book may be outdated though.<br><br>Dawnia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ujaliawolfsdottir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jalia Wolfsdottir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Administratrix</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#330000>(6/28/01 12:03:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> Aye, Dawnia, but it's sort of like being the best watermellon seed spitter on earth. Nifty, but not all that useful... <p><IMG SRC="http://www.bdffl.com/duffl/amy/kahlan_black.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/upluggera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PluggerA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#330000>(10/29/01 2:08:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bow and Arrows?</span><hr size=1> If anyone might need a bow of any sort or arrows please let me know.<br><br>There shall be no fee with the exception of materials and my skills are currently at about 120.<br><br>Plugger <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=9.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=9.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm5.showA